{"id": "EUVD-2025-9398", "enisaUuid": "26b0e2b7-843d-30c5-bdfc-7413888c1970", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: hid-steam: Fix use-after-free when detaching device\n\nWhen a hid-steam device is removed it must clean up the client_hdev used for\nintercepting hidraw access. This can lead to scheduling deferred work to\nreattach the input device. Though the cleanup cancels the deferred work, this\nwas done before the client_hdev itself is cleaned up, so it gets rescheduled.\nThis patch fixes the ordering to make sure the deferred work is properly\ncanceled.", "datePublished": "2025-04-01T15:40:56", "dateUpdated": "2025-04-16T13:19:53", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/026714ec7546de741826324a6a1914c91024d06c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a899adf7063c6745aaff1ec869f3c7f6329ed0a1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ea3f18d2f02629653b7bfe42607737ccd1343e54", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e53fc232a65f7488ab75d03a5b95f06aaada7262"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21923"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "08781702-8d63-3c72-8eaf-ddb65fade146", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.6.79 <6.6.83"}, {"id": "1038c317-f1b9-3b35-9cb6-b9ccdbee4805", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "053fa3888d2a957f4db26c05e503f4c6b9570a30 <ea3f18d2f02629653b7bfe42607737ccd1343e54"}, {"id": "1dc9e221-fe0b-3964-be7c-664e8d5bac30", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e1147961b2145fa61c3078a4a797d9576cde91ab <026714ec7546de741826324a6a1914c91024d06c"}, {"id": "32b43675-d18c-3e19-924e-bff037625b18", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13.4 <6.13.7"}, {"id": "55cb989e-8ce7-3597-abaf-1878ab32f33c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "79504249d7e27cad4a3eeb9afc6386e418728ce0 <e53fc232a65f7488ab75d03a5b95f06aaada7262"}, {"id"